  "Weighted Asset Cost Calculation — a method for valuing assets": "",
  "Wholesale Average Consumer Credit — a lending benchmark": "",
  "Weekly Average Cash Collections — a measure of cash flow": "",
  "Weighted Average Cost of Capital — the blended cost of a company's debt and equity financing": "",
  "WACC is the Weighted Average Cost of Capital. It blends the after-tax cost of debt and the cost of equity, weighted by their proportions in the capital structure. It serves as the minimum hurdle rate for projects.": "",
