  "The amount of money invested in a company": "",
  "The net profit of the company": "",
  "The total revenue a product generates": "",
  "Contribution margin = Price - Variable Cost. It represents the amount each unit sold contributes toward covering fixed costs and generating profit.": "",
  "What does the term 'expected value' mean in financial math?": "",
  "The maximum possible gain": "",
  "The probability-weighted average of all possible outcomes of a financial decision": "",
  "The guaranteed outcome of an investment": "",
  "The value of an asset at maturity": "",
  "Expected value sums each possible outcome multiplied by its probability. It gives the long-run average result of a decision and is essential for evaluating uncertain financial choices.": "",
